 The Abia State Government has warned some group of people planning an unauthorised and illegal coronation of one Sarki Shehu Bello II as the Emir of Aba Emirate Council to stop forthwith or be prepared to face the full weight of the law. This was contained in a statement by the Secretary to Abia State Government, Barr. Chris Ezem, on Wednesday. He directed the immediate cancellation of the proposed illegal coronation, adding that there was nothing like ‘Aba Emirate Council’ in the State. READ ALSO: Over 100 Bullets Found As Gunmen Attack APC Reps. Spokesman In Abia The statement read, “The attention of government of Abia State has been drawn to a proposed coronation of one Sarki Shehu Bello II as the Emir of Aba Emirate Council without recourse to government. “Government further warns all residents in the state especially those resident in Aba to be law abiding. “Law enforcement agents have been directed to swing into action and ensure that no such event capable of breaching the existing peace in the state takes place in Aba or any part of the state.”